I would recommend to move to meson as a first step to fix this. This would get us rid of the disaster that libtool is and make it more transparent how linking is actually done instead of having libtool do magic decisions somewhere in its 10000s of lines of shell code.

Generally there should not be a problem here: cargo is outputting a static PIC library that can be linked into a shared library, or that can become part of another static library (but that requires unpacking and packing again, I'm not sure how/if meson handles that... autotools definitely does not handle it).

